Why LSTM Uses Sigmoid

LSTM has three gates.

Each gate asks a simple question:

"Should I allow this information?"

Sigmoid answers this with a value between 0 and 1.

========

The sigmoid function is one of the most important activation functions in an LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory) network. It is used in all three gates:

Forget Gate
Input Gate
Output Gate

The sigmoid function decides how much information should pass through a gate.

Sigmoid Function
Formula

σ(x)=
1/1+e power of -x
	​

Output Range
0  -------------------------> 1

The output is always between 0 and 1.

0 → Completely block the information
1 → Completely allow the information
0.5 → Allow about half the information

