Role of Sigmoid in LSTM

| Gate        | Uses Sigmoid? | Purpose                                |
| ----------- | ------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Forget Gate | ✅             | Decide what to forget from memory      |
| Input Gate  | ✅             | Decide what new information to store   |
| Output Gate | ✅             | Decide what memory to expose as output |


===

Sigmoid acts like a smart valve in an LSTM. It produces values between 0 and 1, allowing each gate to decide 
how much information to keep, forget, or output. This controlled flow of information is one of the reasons LSTMs can learn long-term dependencies 
much better than standard RNNs.

